python` 2.7 (but not 3.x)\r\n\r\nI suggest that the Python portions of building rustc be made compatible with Python 2.7 and 3.4+.\r\n\r\n- Python 2.7 [will not be maintained upstream after 2020](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0373/#update) (less than three years away)\r\n- On Ubuntu [the plan is to only have Python 3 installed by default](https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Python/3)\r\n- [Python 3 became default stack in Fedora starting in Fedora 23](https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Changes/Python_3_as_Default)\r\n\r\nWhile Python 2 still has a large user base, the trend is moving towards Python 3 becoming the default version, and the only one preinstalled on certain popular Linux distros.\r\n\r\nDoing a cursory look at the code, I don't see any glaring Python 2-only-isms, so it may just work or only require a relatively small amount of effort.\r\n\r\nWould PRs for Python 3 compatibility (which retain compatibility with Python 2) be accepted?", "closed_by": {"login": "Mark-Simulacrum", "id": 5047365, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUwNDczNjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5047365?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum", "html_url": "https://github.com/Mark-Simulacrum", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reaction